Disaster recovery-as-a-service (DRaaS) market is segmented based on service type, service provider, deployment model, organization size, and vertical. The service type segment includes backup and recovery, real-time replication, data protection, and professional services. Businesses can choose services based on their specific recovery needs, whether ensuring data backup, real-time replication for immediate failover, or comprehensive data protection services. The service provider segment consists of managed service providers, cloud service providers, telecom and communication service providers, and others, offering diverse options for DRaaS solutions. Companies can opt for providers that align with their infrastructure requirements and business goals. The deployment model segment covers public cloud, private cloud, and hybrid cloud models, offering flexibility in implementing disaster recovery solutions. Organizations can select deployment models that best suit their existing IT environment and compliance needs. The organization size segment categorizes DRaaS users into small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) and large enterprises, tailoring solutions to suit the scale and complexity of operations. Vertical segmentation includes industries such as BFSI, IT and telecommunications, government and public sector, retail and consumer goods, healthcare, and others, indicating specific sector needs for disaster recovery solutions.

**Market Players**

- IBM Corporation
